The Web Audio API is a powerful, easy to use too for playing and manipulating sound in the browser.  This post will focus on a component called the Analyser Node, which gives us access to real-time data about a sound being played.  We'll use this to create a simple sound visualizer.

If you're unfamiliar with the Web Audio API, here's a simple example showing what you'll need to know to get started.












